result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Yvonne L Zindler was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old), an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. supervisions.notes:
Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program.
Apply 93 days credit.

AMENDED 04-14-2015:  Defendant IS NOT eligible for Earned Release Program.

superMiscConds.notes: AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended.

Reimbursement for Blood Draw costs ($35) to be paid/forwarded to Waukesha Co Clerk of Courts for City of Waukesha Police Department.  To be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision or converted to a civil judgment.
DNA surcharge ($250) to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
Transcript Fee ($22) to be paid/forwarded to Waukesha Co Clerk of Courts for Waukesha County District Attorney's Office or converted to a civil judgment.

Fine is to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.

  If Probation/Extended Supervision is revoked and/or a prison term ordered, outstanding financial obligations shall be collected pursuant to statutory provisions, including deductions from inmate prison monies.  If discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collections may include income assignment.
Psychological evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
Submit to random urine screens.
No use or possession of alcohol, illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.
No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Inform Agent of any and all prescriptions.
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.
Use only one pharmacy.
Not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.
Provide DNA sample if not yet provided.
Attend Victim Impact Panel meeting.
No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged and distributed.
No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (for example, bars, taverns or liquor stores).
